During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki announced that President Biden is expected to meet his goal of administering 200 million COVID-19 vaccine shots in his first 100 days in office. Psaki also mentioned that the President will call on employers to help their employees and communities get vaccinated, including offering tax credits for small- and medium-sized businesses to offset the cost of paid leave for vaccination. Psaki also discussed the President's support for the George Floyd Justice in Policing Act and his intention to work with Congress to pass police reform legislation. She emphasized that the President believes the bar for convicting officers of federal civil rights crimes is too high and needs to be changed. Psaki also addressed questions about the President's commitment to getting the George Floyd bill passed, stating that he will work with Congress and use his influence to push for its passage. Additionally, Psaki discussed the administration's efforts to address vaccine hesitancy and increase access to vaccines, as well as the President's commitment to addressing racial injustice.